page.title: 19WEST END GARAGE,MALBOROUGH
page.content: {West End Garage}is a small garage in Malborough. The man who owns it is called{Mr. Patey. }He has worked there for about{twelve years. }He works about nine or ten hours a day depending how busy he is. He employs two people to work for him. Before the garage was there, there were some cottages. Before that there was a blacksmith's shop. The builders of West End Garage were{Perrott {Brothers of Kingsbridge. }They built the garage between{1930 and 1935. There is a different man who is going to take over the garage soon.
